The Vice President of the United States, Michael R. Pence, recently welcomed the Wounded Warrior Project to the White House. He expressed his admiration for the courage, valor, and determination of servicemen and women who have been injured in the defense of freedom. Pence also hosted a gathering of Gold Star Wives, expressing gratitude and support for their spouses' sacrifice. He emphasized the importance of recognizing and appreciating the sacrifices made by service members and their loved ones. Pence assured that the White House will not overlook or undervalue the sacrifices of the military and pledged to rebuild the military and provide necessary resources and training for the armed forces. As the father of a Marine, Pence expressed pride in standing alongside a President who will fight for men and women in uniform. He concluded by thanking and saluting the brave individuals who have answered the call to serve and promising that their sacrifice will never be in vain.